CE-V5-S42-08 — Proof-Ready Participant Scaffolding
Goal

Prepare the developer kit to become a governed participant in later recursive-governance flows once DEV-UX contract/proof surfaces stabilize.

Why It Matters

S42 should not stop at connection.

It should prepare the first participant for contract and proof participation without prematurely coupling to unstable internals.

By this point in the epic, the developer kit can already become a real external participant in boundary-safe ways:

discover the live boundary

authenticate correctly

inspect identity

retrieve governed context

execute a safe read-only smoke path

That is necessary, but not sufficient.

The developer kit is supposed to become the first governed participant repo in the recursive-governance story. That means it must eventually be able to:

declare participant contract posture

run local verification

assemble proof-bearing outputs

submit those outputs to platform-side proof surfaces

receive verdicts and repair guidance

participate in a full recursive governance cycle

But the platform-side contract/proof surfaces are still stabilizing under DEV-UX.

So the correct move now is not to hardwire unstable assumptions into the developer kit.

The correct move is to create clear proof-ready scaffolding:

enough structure that later integration is easy

enough separation that current supported flows stay honest

enough adapter boundaries that the developer kit remains boundary-consuming, not boundary-defining

This story prepares the first external participant for the next phase without pretending that unfinished platform surfaces are already final.

Story Thesis

The first governed external participant should not jump from:

read-only smoke success

directly into:

tightly coupled contract/proof submission code

Instead, it should establish a disciplined intermediate posture:

contract-shaped participant identity

verification-runner scaffolding

proof-bundle-shaped artifacts

adapter-isolated future integration points

explicit separation between “supported now” and “planned when boundary stabilizes”

That posture is what makes later recursive governance integration clean instead of brittle.

This story creates that posture.

It gives keyhole-developer-kit the shape of a future governed participant without falsely claiming that all proof-bearing flows are already live and stable.

