Implementation Guidance
A) Scaffold the Shape, Not the Final Law

This story is about preparing the participant to connect later.

It is not about locking final platform contract law inside the developer kit.

B) Prefer Adapters Over Direct Coupling

Where future platform integration is expected, use adapters or narrow interfaces rather than scattering future assumptions throughout the repo.

That keeps later updates local and safe.

C) Mark Placeholder Structures Clearly

The repo should make it obvious when something is:

local placeholder shape

future-facing

awaiting platform stabilization

No one should mistake scaffolding for a sealed live contract.

D) Do Not Mine Private Platform Internals for Truth

The developer kit must not solve uncertainty by pulling draft truth directly from private platform code.

That violates the architecture this epic is proving.

E) Preserve Honest Boundaries

This story should strengthen the statement:

the platform defines and publishes

the participant prepares and consumes

F) Keep Current Supported Flows Clean

Do not let placeholder proof scaffolding pollute the current supported read-only experience.

The read-only participant path must remain simple and honest.

