Risks
Risk 1 — Premature Lock-In

If placeholder shapes are mistaken for final platform contract law, later integration becomes harder instead of easier.

Risk 2 — Hidden Coupling to Platform Internals

If builders quietly copy private platform shapes into the developer kit, the external participant boundary is weakened.

Risk 3 — Blurring Supported and Future Behavior

If the repo does not clearly separate supported-now and planned-later flows, users and agents will overestimate current capability.

Risk 4 — Overengineering the Scaffold

If the scaffold becomes too elaborate before platform surfaces stabilize, it creates unnecessary maintenance burden.

Risk 5 — Underbuilding the Scaffold

If everything remains vague and unstructured, later recursive-governance integration becomes chaotic and slow.

